==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epinastic
<hw>Ep`i*nas"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>epi-</ets> + Gr. <?/ pressed close.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>A term applied to that phase of vegetable growth in which an organ
grows more rapidly on its upper than on its under surface. See
<er>Hyponastic</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epineural</ent>⟦br⟧
